race.description: The Hong Kong Jockey Club World Pool (Bm88)
race.comment: A wide-open contest to cap off a blockbuster day. ROCK EMPIRE (14) was gutsy last start at the Kenso, leading all the way and showing grit. Third-up now, drawn well, and ready to go again. WAIMARIE (15) resumes for the Archibald yard and boasts strong fresh form. Her best Victorian figures stack up, and she can fire first-up. WORLD ALLIANCE (10) doesn't possess early dash but packs a lethal finish. Lloyd sticks after a flashing run last start, and the extra trip suits. LORD OF BISCAY (3) caught the eye fresh, then flopped as favourite but had excuses. McDonald staying aboard is a big tick, and sharp improvement is expected. KERGUELEN (7) has talent but faces a sticky draw. He'll be hoping for a hot tempo to unleash late. SIR ARTIE (4) was dominant at Rosehill with a booming finish. He stays at the winning trip but carries more weight. Still, off that last win, he must be respected.
